Seed oils cause inflammation. Canola, corn, sunflower, grapeseed etc..(restaurants cook and coat their pans with these oils⁣

Your tummy bloat is largely inflammation.⁣
⁣
NOT because of MENOPAUSE ⁣
⁣
TIPS on how to Oder⁣
⁣
#1. Tell them you are allergic to seed oils. Technically, you are, since all are toxic ☠️to your health..⁣
⁣
#2. Order chicken, wild fish or red meat 🥩and have it grilled… ask them to use butter instead of any oil.⁣
⁣
✅Hold the sauces.⁣
⁣
What about Starch (complex carb)⁣
⁣
#3. Baked or sweet potato, rice. Mashed potatoes are an ok choice too, but are usually quite high in fat and sometimes they use guar gum 🫣to make it more consistent (avoid this preservative)⁣

Shrimp cocktail, leafy salad with balsamic  only. Speaking of veggies, ask them to hold off on any oils or butter..⁣

Don’t store ANY food in plastic. That includes BPA Free….⁣
⁣
It is not safe. ⁣
⁣
A Known estrogen receptor, and unfortunately it decreases testosterone.⁣
⁣
Plastics can be measured in your body. (a newer test that was invented because of all the plastic usage in the last 20 years) ⁣
⁣
Think about it 🤓A substance that should not be in our bodies at all..⁣
⁣
Plastic products contain chemical additives. A number of these chemicals have been associated with serious health problems such as hormone-related  CANCERS, infertility and neurodevelopment disorders like ADHD and autism.⁣
⁣
** Researchers found that BPA-FREE plastics were still leaching out of material and causing abnormalities in lab mice😱⁣
⁣
This goes for straws, storage containers, utensils, plastic cups…⁣
⁣
WHAT TO STORE YOUR FOOD IN?⁣
⁣
GLASS containers….do a quick search on Amazon and you can find glass meal prep containers.⁣
⁣
Use Paper straws…real utensils in your office ‘snack bag’ just rinse off and wash at home. ⁣
Stainless steel water ‘jugs’ to Take along and refill as you travel. ⁣
⁣
Think about what you consume and how it’s being packaged/ presented ….⁣
Keep it as close to nature as you possibly can…..the least manufacturing steps to your mouth🤗⁣
⁣
Comment below if you want to know how I handle take -out food and ‘left overs’⁣
⁣
⁣

How to Pick up the bar and HIP THRUST⁣
⁣
📹 Like a deadlift- Engage core. Keep back straight (the small of your lower back is neutral)⁣
Get LOW- without rounding your back.⁣
⁣
SQUEEZE your glutes as you lift the bar off the ground.⁣
⁣
* because the bar is extremely close to the ground. Your form is very important here so that you don’t injure your back.⁣
⁣
❌DO NOT just reach down and pick it up with a loose core, loose glutes and around it back. ⁣
⁣
Even though this is only 40 to 50 pounds, that much weight picked up incorrectly could cause injury.⁣
⁣
*notice how close I am to the bench 👀 also sit down with the bar on your hips and slide gently down the bench.⁣
⁣
Always hook shoulder blades onto the bench, keeping head and eyes forward at all times.⁣
⁣
Notice the thoracic, the upper chest and neck are steady and you are moving at your HIPS.⁣
⁣
Give a nice pelvic tilt at the top, and really squeeze the glutes.⁣
⁣
To finish the move safely. Come down on your butt swing your legs to the side and using your obliques and arm muscles, lift the bar up over your legs.⁣
⁣
What do you want to see next comment below👇🏼⁣
⁣
⁣

How to get things done when you are not motivated…I’m NOT MOTIVATED 💯 everyday to workout either.⁣

Adjust mindset…Training, working out and eating wholesome food is something that we GET to do.- It is a privilege and many people don’t have access to nice gyms or quality food choices. ⁣
⁣
Even when You’re NOT motivated, staying the course is much easier with a little prep. ⁣
⁣
⭐️ Train at the same time every day⁣
⭐️ Cook enough food- ONCE- to get 3 to 4 meals out of your effort.⁣
⭐️ Have your gym bag packed well ahead of time (a cute outfit helps😀)⁣
⭐️ Plan out tomorrow when you go to bed tonight (rest easy) ⁣
⁣
Remember: No one is forcing you to diet. It is a choice you are making to become healthier, livelier, stronger and leaner.⁣

Everyday is a new day. It’s always a great reason to celebrate YOU🥰⁣

Revive yourself in THREE minutes. Do you feel like you are falling apart? Just have NO energy ⁣
⁣
Great to do ANY TIME of the day..⁣
when you are feeling a bit stressed or agitated.⁣
⁣
AND as part of a warmup- like HERE💪 back and hips felt great during squats⁣
⁣
📹HIP CIRCLES- Rush blood to your hips, legs and provide the agility you are needing. This really opens up the Lower back too. ⁣
⁣
📹 BIG arm circles- nice n easy. Feel your shoulder joint really open up and become mobile here.⁣
⁣
📹SHOULDER TOSS- bring your shoulders up towards your ears. (alternating like I am) This releases any tension in your neck.⁣
⁣
📹DANCING/ SPINNING in circles- provides spatial awareness, increases oxygen to the brain.⁣
⁣
REPEAT a few times.⁣
⁣
* always done to your favorite jam to boost your spirits even more..⁣
* For me of course 80’s ROCK..⁣
* What is your favorite music to jam out to and feel fantastic.⁣

Think of your goals…vision and HOW you are going to make those happen⁣

Why you gained a pound or two but you’re eating 🥩the same - in menopause.⁣

⁣
However, you didn’t overeat⚖️. If anything, you actually underrate by 200 hundred calories or so a couple of days because you were soo busy.⁣
⁣
Gals on my 1:1 program have a specific caloric amount of food 🍱 to eat each day. ⁣
This is based on their ACTIVITY LEVEL🤸🏽‍♂️ that they will be or ARE doing. ⁣
“Lightly active”⁣
“Moderately active”⁣
“Very active”⁣
⁣
When you SKIP workouts continuously, your caloric needs go down.🔽 Doing Two workouts instead of your normal 5 each week is a big change. ⁣
⁣
3k steps versus 10k daily is also huge over the course of a few weeks.⁣
⁣
This is how you gain weight or stay the same weight (no loss) and still ‘eat the same’ ….or a little less.⁣
⁣
WHAT’S  A GIRL TO DO?⁣
⁣
* Prioritize your training. Get up and get it over with. ⁣
* If you realize after a few skipped days and lackluster steps…reduce over all calories by a few hundred daily (but don’t use this as a ‘normal’ thing ⁣

* You need to strength train for stronger bones, to build Muscle, for Longevity, reduce cancer risk…..yes! to lose fat⁣

New to the gym? Not sure what to do between your sets? ⁣⁣
How long should you rest!?⁣
⁣⁣
Largely depends on what you are lifting and ultimate goals of the training day⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🏋️‍♀️ Example: HEAVY COMPOUND MOVEMENTS such as: squats, deadlifts, bench press PLUS HEAVY hip thrusts, weighted pull ups…heavy farmer walks…⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You should be resting 3-5 minutes or more🙋🏼‍♀️ between every set….on these LARGE GYM LIFTS ⁣
⁣
I will tell you what I do at the bottom👇🏼⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🤓Resting 3–5 minutes between sets leads to greater muscle growth and strength gains than resting one minute, …You have recovered most (~95 %) of your strength and power after just two minutes of rest. To recover near 99%, however, can require resting five minutes or more…PubMed.gov⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🤸🏽‍♂️If you are doing your accessory moments, the goal is to rest very little. These are the more isolated exercises toward the END of your routine.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Such as: hamstring curls, bicep, triceps, abductors…etc…⁣AND db, band training in general. ⁣
⁣⁣
Peek into what I THINK 🤔 ABOUT when resting ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#1. I review my lift (filmed it, 📹Naturally… so I can work on any tweaks that I need to make for the next set.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#2. ALWAYS ADD MORE WEIGHT! I add until I fail…within my appointed reps/sets. **never doing more-it’s prescribed for a reason. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#3. Keep my mind in the game. The Champions mindset is not doing selfies, Posting or looking at Tik Tok right now…literally visualizing lifting more weight. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#4. Glance at my timer… sometimes three minutes seems forever other times I need a full six minutes to RECOVER for the next set.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As a somewhat hyper gal, THIS resting practice took me over a year to get used to..to settle my butt down.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
**harder to do in my garage gym… laundry to switch around, steak to season (post workout) dog to pet🤣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
At least you know why the gym bro’s are taking up the squat rack for 35 minutes..⁣⁣
BIGGER AND STRONGER MUSCLES 🤗💪⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Drop me a chat about your resting habits⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

Three mistakes I made along the way.⁣
⁣
Beginning my fit💪 and wellness journey at 16 was easy for me. I simply loved everything about it.⁣
⁣
My dad pushed the nutritional 🤓coursework and even in 1985, we talked to schools about their executive wellness degrees. ⁣
⁣
There were just two schools in Florida that actually offered such a degree in the late 80’s. Forward thinking for the times.⁣
⁣
I’ve learned a lot these last almost 40 years since and here’s how I messed up along the way. ⁣
⁣
#.1 Totally caught up in the skinny culture of the 80’s/90’s. Sure, my genetics have me on the thin side but I adopted a lower calorie/ low fat diet for decades. ⁣
⁣
* Causing me to me exhausted trying to raise sons. Skinny fat syndrome ushered in.⁣
⁣
#2. Didn’t eat enough animal protein. We were brought up on our disastrous food pyramid with 9 servings of grains 🍞🥯🥐daily. Worst thing is I raised my sons according to it☹️⁣
⁣
#3. Over trained/ under recovered. This took me well into my 40’s. ⁣
* consequences of under eating, doing too much and not sleeping enough. ⁣
* Got used to taking naps everyday  and being super tired. Just being a mom🤷‍♀️⁣
⁣
What my lifestyle is like now⁣
⁣
✅ I eat to build muscle and for strength. Means, prioritize animal protein, and eating at maintenance, surplus ⬆️and some deficit ⬇️days. ⁣
⁣
*This keeps metabolism up also since I’m giving my body the necessary nutrients it needs and mixing up my calories. ⁣
⁣
✅ I train for strength not to be thin. ⁣
Means 4 days a week mostly. (Some seasons 5) Gives me 3 full days of rest to recover fully. ⁣
⁣
Bodies build lean muscle at REST⁣
⁣
* This was by far, the hardest for me to do. I’m a hyper gal who likes to do a LOT. This took me two full years to actually ‘recover from’ ⁣
⁣
⁣
This is a long-term journey. A journey of health and VITALITY. Not something that you can usually comprehend over night. ⁣
⁣
Give yourself grace, patience and time ⌛️⁣
Implement the daily changes that are needed to keep your body healthy and disease-free.🙏⁣

Motivation is unreliable.⁣
⁣
That’s why we put down the rails of practice, habit and repetition in my coaching programs.⁣
⁣
Motivation often comes AFTER action.⁣
⁣
The more you ‘do’ 🐜 the more motivated you’ll become. ⁣
⁣
The more you get into your routine🏋️‍♀️, the less fickle-motivation and jumping around in different programs and diets. ⁣
⁣
☑️TOP TIPS FOR THE WEEK AHEAD⁣
⁣
🤓 Reduce distractions⁣
🤓 Focus on ONE thing at a time. ⁣
⁣
Ie: MONDAY-Hook up MFP. Pull out your kitchen scale ⁣
Tuesday- Track and measure breakfast⁣
Wednesday- Eat the same breakfast and track/measure lunch⁣
Thursday- Track/ Measure breakfast and lunch⁣
Friday- Track and measure dinner⁣
Saturday- work on tracking and measuring all three meals ⁣
Sunday- add snacks into MFP⁣
⁣
** You will have almost all of your regular food logged so it won’t be so tedious the second week of tracking* ⁣
⁣
Week 2: REPEAT and try to add every meal to MFP or your favorite calorie/ macro tracker.⁣
If it’s too rushed, go back to week one. Don’t feel pressure to track every meal if you are brand new to tracking. ⁣
⁣
🤓Putting down new Habits and routines require patience and single-task concentration⁣

Are you at risk for dementia? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
ALL menopausal women have some degree of increased risk when estrogen drops🔽⁣⁣
⁣⁣
More women than men get it, According to the Alzheimer’s Society. It is believed that estrogen plays a role. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As you go through menopause. Your estrogen levels drop significantly. Unless you go on hormone replacement (BHRT), hormones will bottom out at an all time low ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This increases your risk of developing dementia and Alzheimer’s. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Alzheimer's is characterised by a build-up of amyloid-β and tau proteins in the brain. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Research (Nat.Institute on Aging 7/22) has shown that estrogen may help to protect the brain from Alzheimer's by blocking some of the harmful effects of amyloid-β protein.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I have a dementia gene(one) raising my risk by 3-fold. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Mama has dementia. I had a feeling I was at risk too ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So I decided to take action even BEFORE I got tested ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Here’s what I did based on the CURRENT research known to help prevent dementia. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. EXERCISE- @hubermanlab researched and found this to be the #1 thing you can do to prevent it .⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2. WORK your brain- solution: I started a business. My brain works 10-12 hours a day once again. ⁣⁣
*You can do Crosswords, mind-games and work on puzzles to help. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3. STAY social- friends and a community link has shown to help prevent this neurological brain disorder ⁣⁣
⁣
4. EAT plenty of PROTEIN- feeds the brain. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
There are still many unknowns but estrogen seems to play a role ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Take 10 minutes and research if you want to know the latest data.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
** testing for the gene was done by my functional doctor , as part of a myriad of tests I get to check my overall health ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

⁣
How can elevating your heels help In the squat?⁣
⁣
▪️ Mobility- By shifting the center of gravity back, it allows your hips to sink deeper into the squat.⁣
⁣
▪️Less Back Compression- This increases engagement of your quads, versus flat feet. ⁣
⁣
*It also decreases the compression of the lumbar (low back👍🏻) ⁣
⁣
▪️ Build strength in the ‘hole’ - at BHWellness, we teach ALL ladies to squat to parallel. (Bodyweight, DB and barbell) ⁣
⁣
* It’s crucial to squat to parallel, and we analyze mobility, agility, ankle stabilization via video feedback📹. ⁣
⁣
▪️When you squat down to parallel, you are recruiting the whole posterior chain versus just using your quads, (not going to parallel) which will lead to muscle imbalances and knee pain😩⁣
⁣
HOW OFTEN to use a plate? ⁣
⁣
Like most exercises, it’s important to vary your stance often. Meaning, don’t use the same bar, grip, stance, sets and reps over and over. ⁣
⁣
I squat on a plate a few times a year, as needed. ⁣
⁣
Part of my unique Conjugate style of training that I do and all of my 1:1 clients💪⁣

Stop bloat with LowFodMap’s⁣
⁣
🔼 Tag a buddy who suffers from bloat.⁣
⁣
Nutrition is not about ONE single diet that will keep you healthy, strong, lean and full of energy. ⁣
⁣
However, having an arsenal of ‘what to eat’ or NOT EAT to keep you from being bloated can be pretty helpful. ⁣
⁣
My son came down with Crohn’s disease at age 11. That turned our world upside down.⁣
⁣
Many trips through his teen years to Boston Children’s Hospital taught us all HOW to eat and avoid bloat, cramps 🤢and gassy pain. ⁣
⁣
WHAT ARE ‘FODS’:⁣
FODMAPs are a group of sugars that are not completely digested or absorbed in our intestines. ⁣
⁣
When FODMAPs reach the small intestine, they move slowly, attracting water. When they pass into the large intestine, FODMAPs are fermented by gut bacteria, producing gas as a result.⁣
⁣
For people without IBD, like me, I have found when I adhere to the quantity of LowFods,  my energy level stays steady- never drains.⁣
⁣
Example: In the slide ⏩️ a whole apple is high in fructose and sorbitol. However, eating just a 1/4 cup of an apple, lowers fructose and sorbitol to an acceptable level- for someone with IBD. ⁣
⁣
I tend to follow the recommendation.⁣
⁣
This is not an exhaustive list. I’m also hypothyroid. So I avoid all gluten. Nutrition should be VERY customized to the individual self.⁣
⁣
Plus, we avoid seed oils, Preservatives, food dyes, GMO’s and any processed food. We do that for health, longevity and vitality. ⁣
⁣
That’s me though. You see, Nutrition is extremely individual. Foods react differently with each person. ⁣
⁣
If you suffer from bloat, LowFodMap could be used part of an elimination diet. That is what we did with my son. ⁣
⁣
Take away everything and slowly add food back in, your body will tell you what YOU can’t tolerate. ⁣
⁣
This app is from Monash University. It’s handy and easy to use.😀 at the time it was the only app available. I like the red, green yellow light icons of the app.⁣
⁣
⁣
.⁣
.⁣
#lowfodmap #macrocoach #bloatfree #womenover40 #momover40 #fitover45 #eatmore #antiinflammatorydiet #lowfodmapdiet

How much weight can you hip thrust WITH NO HANDS? ⁣

This may look gimmicky but I do this to assure I’m using my hips/ glutes NOT MY ENTIRE BODY. ⁣
⁣

By holding your head securely, this keeps the upper body from moving. ⁣
⁣
This puts all of the load on the hips and glutes. BINGO🍑⁣
⁣
Start off easy and add weight every set. ⁣
⁣
What I did WITHOUT HANDS: ⁣
145lb x 20 (I always warm up with 145)⁣
185 x 12⁣
205 x 10⁣
225 x 10⁣
245 x 4 no hands + a few with hands. ⁣
⁣
This also ensures that my glutes are working together, versus one side taking over. If your barbell tilts, then you know which side to work on. ⁣
⁣
Glutes, core, quads and hammies are at work here. Don’t skip your thrusting, if you want strong, perky glutes💪⁣

Afraid to lose the dump truck.🍑⁣
⁣
There comes a time in the muscle growth process that you probably think 🤔 when to really lean out. ⁣
⁣
As I tweaked things this summer to lose a few pounds that I had gained 🫣I’m always careful not to eat in a deficit ⁣
⁣
Eating in a chronic calorie deficit is the quickest way to lose any muscle gains, especially if you are over 40 or 50.⁣
⁣
* starting at age 30, we lose 3 to 8% of muscle mass per decade. The rate accelerates after age 60.⁣
⁣

MY CORE FOUR⁣⁣
1. Lift heavy weights.  At least progressively heavier for YOU.⁣⁣
⁣
2. Minimize processed foods- anything in a package, preservatives, HFCS, hydrogenated oils, food dyes and ALL PLASTIC containers. ⁣⁣
⁣
**ALL endocrine disrupters-mess with estrogen and plastics kill testosterone. ⁣⁣
Eat ample animal protein and AVOID  non- fat or low fat food ⁣⁣
⁣
3. WALK outside over terrain and hills -A LOT. We need movement for joints, tendons, ligaments and metabolic health ⁣⁣
⁣
4. Use sunblock on face, neck and chest🔑⁣
⁣⁣
❌You don’t NEED supplements, protein powder, cold baths, saunas or any other outside influence that KEEPS you from the CORE 4. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

⁣⁣
EASY? Yes, but takes TIME to remember,  implement and replace the bad habits.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
SOOO just LIFT🏋️‍♀️⁣⁣
If you can’t remember ANYTHING else. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Well, use sunblock or you’ll be super sad at my age😩⁣⁣

P.S. If you are 40-60yrs. Implement quicker. Lift, walk then work on changing your food. (Hardest of the 4) ⁣⁣

Say goodbye to jiggly arms. ⁣
Why train upper body?⁣
⁣
It’s cool n all to have a strong lower body and many gals ignore upper bodywork altogether. ⁣
⁣
To have the best symmetry, composition AND overall strength, don’t skip ‘back/chest’ day. ⁣
⁣
📹DB BENCH- No need for a barbell. Be sure your elbows POINT to the floor NOT flared out. Keep arms close to torso ⁣
⁣
LANDMINE KNEELING PRESS- keep opposite hand OFF thigh. This ensures your OBLIQUES are fired. In order to complete this move without wobbling, your core must be super tight.⁣
⁣
SEATED ROW- Squeeze your scapula..Think shoulder blades together as you pull the cable toward your torso.⁣
⁣
** Usually, I would do some sort of tricep exercise along with these -to further ‘tone’ the back of the arms. ⁣
⁣
Tell me your favorite upper body exercises or something that you would like to see💪⁣

Gals on ALL my programs have at least TWO full upper body days a week.⁣
